# Hamrin.ai Design System

**BEFORE writing any frontend/UI code, read `DESIGN_BRIEF.md` at the project root.**

## Quick Reference

### Fonts
- **Headlines (hero, section titles):** Lora serif (`font-[family-name:var(--font-lora)]`)
- **Everything else:** Inter sans-serif (default)

### Colors
- **Primary CTA:** `bg-[#1E40AF]` (deep blue)
- **Logo accent:** `text-[#EAB308]` (golden yellow)
- **Success/checks:** `text-green-500` / `bg-green-500`
- **Hero bg:** `from-[#FDF8EF] via-[#FEFCF7] to-white` (warm cream gradient)
- **Body bg:** white or `bg-gray-50` for alternating sections

### Rules
1. NO dark backgrounds on landing page — warm and light always
2. NO sans-serif for hero/section headlines — use Lora serif
3. NO emerald/teal as primary action color — primary is deep blue
4. Feature pills use soft pastel bg + darker text of same hue
5. Cards: white bg, gray-200 border, rounded-xl, shadow-lg
6. Generous spacing: py-20 to py-24 between major sections
7. Max width 1200px for nav/footer, 800px for hero text, 1100px for feature grids
8. Testimonial key phrases have yellow underline decoration
9. Browser frame mocks have 3 colored dots (green, yellow, red)
10. Uppercase labels: text-xs font-semibold text-gray-400 tracking-[0.2em]
